nodes.text: Eating-paper was a type of foodstuff that was served at the Canto Casino Hotel in the city of Canto Bight on the planet Cantonica. In 34 ABY, the Wermal salesbeing Kedpin Shoklop noticed eating-papers among the food served during midmeal at the Canto Casino Hotel.

Eating-paper was first mentioned in Saladin Ahmed's 2017 short story "Rules of the Game," written for the novella collection Canto Bight, which was released as part of the Journey to Star Wars: The Last Jedi multimedia project.
